	Associate Professor <br>
	Department of Agricultural Economics<br>
	Kansas State University<br>
	(nvilloria at ksu dot edu)
      </p>

      <p> My research program has two main thrusts: global land use
      and international trade. Currently I'm exploring how future
      climates might shape world food markets. I also investigate the
      competition between agricultural land and forest resources as
      global agriculture faces mounting pressures to satisfy growing
      demands for food and biofuels.  </p>

